The use of plateau pressure may not be a good surrogate for pulmonary stress inferred based on end-inspiratory P L and has been shown to be imprecise in predicting an end-inspiratory P L higher than 25cmH 2O. (
36
) Moreover, the main disadvantage is that it disregards the pressure from wich the V T is delivered, that is, PEEP. In spite of the above limitations, levels higher than 30 cmH 2O remain useful predictors of mortality. (
37
)
